comments[5]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-23T11:26:20.051Z",codex-root,"Duplicate-check evidence: searched all-status tracker data for 'deps tree OOM memory', 'dependency graph cycle memory exhaustion', and 'deps format tree'. Existing pm-8kch covers missing-reference parity, pm-x85o the original visualization, pm-ju83 graph primitives, pm-9rxu scale, and pm-4k6b bounded context, but none tracks tree-format memory exhaustion. Reproduction observed during pm-kr3t orientation; the process grew to roughly 4 GB before termination. This item remains open and unclaimed because it was documented, not implemented, in the current SDK/digital-twin tranche."
  "2026-07-23T20:33:24.846Z",claude-code-agent,"Implementation start 2026-07-23: actively deliver the shared bounded/streamable read projection surface across pm-gygna8, pm-a9mc, pm-ishm, and pm-646c. Scope includes public SDK contracts, thin CLI/MCP wiring, deterministic bounds, token-efficient projections, pipeline behavior, docs, contracts, focused regressions, exact coverage, and packed/manual consumer proof. All-status duplicate review reused these canonical items and their closed prerequisites; no parallel implementation item was created."
  "2026-07-23T21:01:51.712Z",claude-code-agent,"Implementation evidence: tree/graph dependency projections now apply deterministic default or explicit depth/node/edge/token budgets, avoid recursive graph conversion, and report reasons/limits/full totals/omitted counts; cyclic and multiply-linked fixtures pass."
  "2026-07-23T21:13:06.996Z",claude-code-agent,"Acceptance evidence: packed temporary tracker with a dependency cycle respected node/edge/token bounds and reported node_limit plus total_edge_count=2 and omitted_edge_count=1 without recursive expansion."
  "2026-07-23T21:19:09.300Z",claude-code-agent,"Final verification evidence: full sandboxed repository coverage passed 349 files / 6,189 tests at exact Statements 42,435/42,435, Branches 30,059/30,059, Functions 8,645/8,645, Lines 41,245/41,245. Typecheck, ESLint, zero-duplication, static quality, 100% docstrings, package boundary, token budgets, docs/skills, contracts, context evaluation, linked tests, and packed consumer acceptance also passed."
